#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.48"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.48:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.48:0.2"
msgid "5. Uposathavagga"
msgstr "5. Sabbath"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 48. Nakulamātāsutta → nakulamātumanāpakāyikasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.48:0.3"
msgid "48. Nakulamātāsutta"
msgstr "48. With Nakula’s Mother on the Loveable Gods"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.268"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: susumāragire → suṃsumāragire (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an8.48:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile "
"Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood."

msgctxt "an8.48:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho nakulamātā gahapatānī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā … "
"pe …. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho nakulamātaraṃ gahapatāniṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then the housewife Nakula’s mother went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat "
"down to one side. The Buddha said to her:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Aṭṭhahi kho, nakulamāte, dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"“Nakula’s mother, when they have eight qualities females—when their body "
"breaks up, after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Loveable "
"Group."

msgctxt "an8.48:2.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "an8.48:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, nakulamāte, mātugāmo yassa mātāpitaro bhattuno denti atthakāmā "
"hitesino anukampakā anukampaṃ upādāya tassa hoti pubbuṭṭhāyinī "
"pacchānipātinī kiṅkārapaṭissāvinī manāpacārinī piyavādinī. (1)"
msgstr ""
"Take the case of a female whose mother and father give her to a husband "
"wanting what’s best for her, out of kindness and compassion. She would get "
"up before him and go to bed after him, and be obliging, behaving nicely and "
"speaking politely."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:3.1"
msgid "Ye te bhattu garuno honti—"
msgstr ""
"She honors, respects, esteems, and venerates those her husband respects, "
"such as"

msgctxt "an8.48:3.2"
msgid "mātāti vā pitāti vā samaṇabrāhmaṇāti vā—"
msgstr "mother and father, and ascetics and brahmins."

msgctxt "an8.48:3.3"
msgid ""
"te sakkaroti garuṃ karoti māneti pūjeti, abbhāgate ca āsanodakena "
"paṭipūjeti. (2)"
msgstr "And when they arrive she serves them with a seat and water."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:4.1"
msgid ""
"Ye te bhattu abbhantarā kammantā—uṇṇāti vā kappāsāti vā—tattha dakkhā hoti "
"analasā tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgatā alaṃ kātuṃ alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ. (3)"
msgstr ""
"She’s skilled and tireless in her husband’s household duties, such as "
"knitting and sewing. She understands how to go about things in order to "
"complete and organize the work."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:5.1"
msgid "Yo so bhattu abbhantaro antojano—dāsāti vā pessāti vā kammakarāti vā—"
msgstr ""
"She knows what work her husband’s domestic bondservants, employees, and "
"workers have completed, and what they’ve left incomplete."

msgctxt "an8.48:5.2"
msgid ""
"tesaṃ katañca katato jānāti akatañca akatato jānāti, gilānakānañca balābalaṃ "
"jānāti khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyañcassa paccaṃsena saṃvibhajati. (4)"
msgstr ""
"She knows who is sick, and who is fit or unwell. She distributes to each a "
"fair portion of various foods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:6.1"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ bhattā āharati dhanaṃ vā dhaññaṃ vā rajataṃ vā jātarūpaṃ vā taṃ "
"ārakkhena guttiyā sampādeti, tattha ca hoti adhuttī athenī asoṇḍī avināsikā. "
"(5)"
msgstr ""
"She ensures that any income her husband earns is guarded and protected, "
"whether money, grain, silver, or gold. She doesn’t overspend, steal, waste, "
"or lose it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:7.1"
msgid ""
"Upāsikā kho pana hoti buddhaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā dhammaṃ saraṇaṃ gatā saṅghaṃ "
"saraṇaṃ gatā. (6)"
msgstr ""
"She’s a lay follower who has gone for refuge to the Buddha, his teaching, "
"and the Saṅgha."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:8.1"
msgid "Sīlavatī kho pana hoti—"
msgstr "She’s ethical."

msgctxt "an8.48:8.2"
msgid ""
"pāṇātipātā paṭiviratā … pe … surāmerayamajjapamādaṭṭhānā paṭiviratā … pe …. "
"(7)"
msgstr ""
"She doesn’t kill living creatures, steal, commit sexual misconduct, lie, or "
"use alcoholic drinks that cause negligence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli4.269"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:9.1"
msgid ""
"Cāgavatī kho pana hoti vigatamalamaccherena cetasā agāraṃ ajjhāvasati "
"muttacāgā payatapāṇinī vossaggaratā yācayogā dānasaṃvibhāgaratā. (8)"
msgstr ""
"She’s generous. She lives at home rid of the stain of stinginess, freely "
"generous, open-handed, loving to let go, committed to charity, loving to "
"give and to share."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:10.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, nakulamāte, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato mātugāmo kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā manāpakāyikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjatīti."
msgstr ""
"When they have these eight qualities females—when their body breaks up, "
"after death—are reborn in company with the Gods of the Loveable Group."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:11.1"
msgid "Yo naṃ bharati sabbadā,"
msgstr "She’d never look down on her husband,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:11.2"
msgid "niccaṃ ātāpi ussuko;"
msgstr "who’s always keen to work hard,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:11.3"
msgid "Taṃ sabbakāmadaṃ posaṃ,"
msgstr "always looking after her,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:11.4"
msgid "bhattāraṃ nātimaññati."
msgstr "and bringing whatever she wants."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:12.1"
msgid "Na cāpi sotthi bhattāraṃ,"
msgstr "And a good woman never scolds her husband"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:12.2"
msgid "issāvādena rosaye;"
msgstr "with jealous words."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:12.3"
msgid "Bhattu ca garuno sabbe,"
msgstr "Being astute, she reveres"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:12.4"
msgid "paṭipūjeti paṇḍitā."
msgstr "those respected by her husband."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:13.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhāhikā analasā,"
msgstr "She gets up early, works tirelessly,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:13.2"
msgid "saṅgahitaparijjanā;"
msgstr "and manages the domestic help."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:13.3"
msgid "Bhattu manāpaṃ carati,"
msgstr "She’s loveable to her husband,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:13.4"
msgid "sambhataṃ anurakkhati."
msgstr "and preserves his wealth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "an8.48:14.1"
msgid "Yā evaṃ vattati nārī,"
msgstr "A lady who fulfills these duties"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:14.2"
msgid "bhattu chandavasānugā;"
msgstr "according to her husband’s desire,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Manāpā nāma te → manāpakāyikā (si, mr)
msgctxt "an8.48:14.3"
msgid "Manāpā nāma te devā,"
msgstr "is reborn among the gods"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.48:14.4"
msgid "yattha sā upapajjatī”ti."
msgstr "called ‘Loveable’.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.48:14.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
